  "title": "Newtons second law - block between two objects",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a block located at the middle of an inclined surface that slants upward and to the right. A box is placed on top of a block. A string extends parallel to the inclined surface starting from the right side of the box and attaching to a vertical wall at the top of the incline.\" src=\"/images/bc94b422d96efefb93d16d05276daef2.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block is held in place on a rough ramp. A box, which is larger in size than the block, is attached by a string to a wall at the top of the ramp. The box is at rest on top of the block, and there is negligible friction between them. When the block is released, it begins to slide down the ramp with initial acceleration <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub 1\"><math alttext=\"a sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>. Then, additional mass is added to the box, the procedure is repeated, and the block begins sliding with initial acceleration <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub 2\"><math alttext=\"a sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>. Which of the following correctly compares <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub 1\"><math alttext=\"a sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub 2\"><math alttext=\"a sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> and provides a valid justification?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i1",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub 2 is less than a sub 1\"><math alttext=\"a sub 2 is less than a sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> because the additional mass of the block-box system increases the force of friction exerted on the block by the ramp.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub 2 is less than a sub 1\"><math alttext=\"a sub 2 is less than a sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> because the tension in the string becomes larger to support the additional weight in the box.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub 2 equals a sub 1\"><math alttext=\"a sub 2 equals a sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> because the force of friction between the block and the box is negligible.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a sub 2 equals a sub 1\"><math alttext=\"a sub 2 equals a sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> because the component of the weight force parallel to the ramp increases in proportion to the mass of the box-block system.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
